To find the value of x, we need to isolate x on one side of the equation. The equation is x + 5 = 12. 

First, we want to get x by itself, so we need to get rid of the +5 on the same side as x. We can do this by subtracting 5 from both sides of the equation. 

So, x + 5 - 5 = 12 - 5. This simplifies to x = 7.
